## Project Overview

**Project Name:** Spontaneity Fit  
**Type:** Full-Stack Web Application with Authentication  
**Purpose:** Instant workout generator with user accounts and workout tracking  
**Problem Solved:** Many people struggle with workout monotony and don't know what exercises to do at the gym. They also need a way to track their progress.  
**Solution:** A RESTful API that generates randomized, customized workout routines based on user preferences (target area and available equipment), with user authentication and the ability to save and track workout progress.

### Technology Stack
- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- **Backend:** Node.js with Express.js
- **Database:** MongoDB with Mongoose
- **Authentication:** JWT (JSON Web Tokens) with crypto-based password hashing
- **Deployment:** Render.com (Backend), MongoDB Atlas (Database)

---

## Project Structure

```
/SpontaneityFit-API
  |-- /client              ‚Üê Frontend (what users see)
  |   |-- index.html       ‚Üê The webpage structure with auth & app views
  |   |-- style.css        ‚Üê Styling including auth forms & saved workouts
  |   |-- app.js           ‚Üê Handles auth, workout generation & saving
  |
  |-- /models              ‚Üê Database blueprints
  |   |-- Exercise.js      ‚Üê Defines what an exercise looks like
  |   |-- User.js          ‚Üê Defines user account structure
  |   |-- SavedWorkout.js  ‚Üê Defines saved workout structure
  |
  |-- /middleware          ‚Üê Authentication middleware
  |   |-- auth.js          ‚Üê JWT token verification
  |
  |-- .env                 ‚Üê Secret configuration (database password, JWT secret)
  |-- .gitignore           ‚Üê Tells Git what NOT to upload
  |-- db.js                ‚Üê Connects to MongoDB database
  |-- index.js             ‚Üê Main server (the brain of the backend)
  |-- seed-enhanced.js     ‚Üê Populates database with 30+ exercises
  |-- package.json         ‚Üê Lists all dependencies (libraries needed)
```

